  "body": "\r\n### What's your issue about?\r\nIs there any reason in the ERC20 standard in Vyper the ``decimals`` is not public?\r\nLike here: https://github.com/ethereum/vyper/blob/master/examples/tokens/ERC20.v.py\r\nIn line 17 ``decimals: int128`` is not public.\r\nAlso decimals is not accessible from the premade ERC20 contract.\r\nHowever, in the vypercoin implementation the decimals is public.\r\nIf there is no reason for that I will add it to the code and submit a PR.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed?\r\n\r\n``decimals: public(int128)``\r\nAnd adding it to the premade contract as well.\r\n\r\n#### Cute Animal Picture\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10667901/37700397-09d31d6e-2cf4-11e8-8da5-8aa233bbbf49.png)\r\n\r\n",
